nodes.title: Latent Interpolate RATIO Note
widgets_values:
Scale by> Upscale amount

Denoise for Upscale> Amount of change (higher=more changes to the original image)

Latent Interpolate RATIO>

lower= latent dominant
higher= lanczos dominant
use 0.4+ to remove upscale artifacts
Denoise for Upscale= 0.15+
Area method reduces banding artifacts further

TIP> as you get denoise for upscale higher, you can lower the latent interpolate ratio, however the node group is aimed for solving issues with low denoise

A wide, night or evening after sunset low-angle shot of a group of archeologists working in an ancient Egyptian burial site in a desert oasis, creating a suspenseful atmosphere. The scene is framed with diagonal lines, using a double complementary (tetradic) color palette and multi-colored chiaroscuro lighting. Realistic dim volumetric lighting casts dramatic shadows, emphasizing the archeologists' focused expressions as they meticulously clean and examine artifacts. The background features a lush oasis with palm trees, contrasting with the arid desert. Film grain and subtle color grading enhance the documentary-style realism, with a warm, golden hue adding to the mysterious ambiance. A group of archaeologists, with diverse ethnicities and skin tones, work meticulously in an ancient Egyptian burial site under a desert oasis. The lead archaeologist, a middle-aged woman with sun-kissed skin and determined eyes, carefully cleans a newly discovered artifact. Her colleague, a younger man with olive skin and a curious expression, examines a nearby hieroglyphic wall. The scene is bathed in a double complementary (tetradic) color palette, with warm desert tones and cool shadows. The lighting is multi-colored, using chiaroscuro to create deep, dramatic contrasts. Soft, golden sunlight filters through the oasis trees, while spotlights illuminate the excavation site, enhancing the suspenseful atmosphere. The composition is documentary-style, with a realistic, grainy texture and subtle color grading that emphasizes the historical and mysterious nature of the site.
